name: final-critical-habitat-for-the-whooping-crane-grus-americanad0d44
notes: To provide the user with a general idea of areas where the final critical habitat for Whooping crane (Grus americana) occur based on the description provided in the Federal Register. The geographic extent includes Barton, Rena, Rice and Stafford counties in Kansas ; Adams, Buffalo, Dawson, Hall, Kearny and Phelps counties in Nebraska ; Alfalfa county, Oklahoma ; and Aransas, Calhoun and Refugio counties in Texas.
